From 1ef19df54e1e2c1d2da42f2d7b5522fafa0bb5f4 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Micheal Waltz <micheal@ecliptik.com>
Date: Sat, 25 Apr 2026 13:38:12 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] sdl3: programmatic
 SDL_SetHintWithPriority(INVALID_PARAM_CHECKS, "0") on DOS
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Bisect/diagnostic patch for Phase 7 black-screen + drawSurface-invalid
flood. The 0028 patch ruled out NULL textures from the two silent
NXEngine creation sites (Renderer.cpp:189 spot_light, Font.cpp:75 atlas
push_back) — neither LOG_ERROR fires, so both creates succeed.

That leaves two leads. This patch tests one of them cheaply:

Lead 2: SDL_object_validation is still true at render time, despite the
launcher exporting SDL_INVALID_PARAM_CHECKS=0 via DOSBox-X's COMMAND.COM
SET. Env var DOES reach the DOS process (verified via getenv probe in
sdltest.c during task #5), but SDL3's hint pipeline only flips
SDL_object_validation false when SDL_AddHintCallback fires its initial
callback during SDL_SetObjectValid — and the env value is read at that
moment. If for any DOS-init-order reason the env read returns
NULL/empty at that point, validation_enabled stays true and every
texture not in the validation hash trips Parameter 'texture' is invalid
in CHECK_TEXTURE_MAGIC.

Fix shape: call SDL_SetHintWithPriority before SDL_Init at OVERRIDE
priority. By the time SDL_Init's internal SDL_SetObjectValid registers
the hint callback, the value is already in the property bag and the
callback fires with a known-good "0".

Why DOS needs this: only the DOS build has the env-via-COMMAND.COM-SET
delivery path. Desktop builds typically inherit env from the parent
shell, where the env-read timing isn't fragile. Guarded by NXE_DOS to
avoid changing desktop behaviour either way until we confirm whether
this is the fix.

Three possible outcomes after smoke:
- (A) drawSurface 'invalid' count drops to ~0 → confirms the
  env-read-timing hypothesis; this patch becomes the fix.
- (B) Count unchanged → validation hash isn't the issue; revert and
  pivot to instrumenting drawSurface to identify NULL-texture sources.
- (C) Mixed → both factors at play; further analysis required.

Single-line change, clean revert if (B). Per task #5 bisect's confirmed
ground truth that SDL_INVALID_PARAM_CHECKS=0 cannot suppress NULL
textures (NULL guard at SDL_utils_c.h:79 precedes the validation short-
circuit), this patch ONLY helps if the errors come from the hash-
lookup path on non-NULL pointers — not from literal NULL textures.
---
 src/main.cpp | 12 ++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 12 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/main.cpp b/src/main.cpp
index 972a766..8c2070a 100644
--- a/src/main.cpp
+++ b/src/main.cpp
@@ -303,6 +303,18 @@ int main(int argc, char *argv[])
 
   Logger::init(ResourceManager::getInstance()->getPrefPath("debug.log"));
 //  SDL_LogSetAllPriority(SDL_LOG_PRIORITY_VERBOSE);
+
+#ifdef NXE_DOS
+  // Force-disable SDL3's object-validation hash lookup before SDL_Init so the
+  // hint is in place when the first SDL_SetObjectValid call (inside SDL_Init's
+  // renderer/texture paths) registers SDL_InvalidParamChecksChanged via
+  // SDL_AddHintCallback. Equivalent to setting SDL_INVALID_PARAM_CHECKS=0 in
+  // the environment, but at OVERRIDE priority and unconditionally — sidesteps
+  // any env-read-timing concerns. Diagnostic for the Phase 7 black-screen /
+  // 1647-drawSurface-invalid-error bug.
+  SDL_SetHintWithPriority(SDL_HINT_INVALID_PARAM_CHECKS, "0", SDL_HINT_OVERRIDE);
+#endif
+
   // SDL3: SDL_Init returns bool (true on success); old `< 0` check would always be false.
   if (!SDL_Init(SDL_INIT_VIDEO | SDL_INIT_AUDIO))
   {
